Problem Solving Schema
----------------------

It has the following information with it.
1) Problem Description (optional, but recommended).
   1.1 Name of the Problem
   1.2 Problem ID
   1.3 Name of the User
   1.4 Purpose
   
2) Task Files
   For each task,
   2.1 Task Id
   2.2 Task Priority
   2.3 Dependencies
   2.4 Approximate Timeout (optional, but recommended)
   2.5 Task Source File Path
   2.6 Task Input Set Path
   2.7 Task Output Set Path
   2.8 Task Compile Command
   2.9 Task Execution Command
   
3) Result Compilation Program
   3.1 RCP Source File Path
   
4) Execution Manager Program (optional, but recommended)
   4.1 EMP Source File Path


The problem schema has to be in the following XML format.

<problem>
	<description>
			<name></name>
    			<problemid></id>
			<user></user>
			<purpose></purpose>
	</description>

	<tasks>
		<task>
			<taskid></taskid>
			<taskpriority></taskpriority>
			<dependencies>	
					<do>TaskID</do>
			<dependencies>
			<tasktimeout>
			</tasktimeout>
			<tasksourcepath>
			</tasksourcepath>
			<taskinputsetpath>
			</taskinputsetpath>
			<taskoutputsetpath>
			</taskoutputsetpath>
			<taskcompilecommand>
			</taskcompilecommand>
			<taskexecutioncommand>
			</taskexecutioncommand>


                </task>
	</tasks>

	
	
	<rcp>
		<rcpsourcepath>
		</rcpsourcepath>
	</rcp>

	<emp>
		<empsourcepath>
		</empsourcepath>
	</emp>
</problem>

The PSS is used by the Grid Computing Framework, to collect the components and tools it needs to solve the problem. The data in the PSS should be thoroughly checked before submitting the PSS.
